# Avo Resources

Avo resources are Ruby classes under the `Avo::Resources::RESOURCE_NAME` module. They usually sit in the [app/avo/resources/](mdc:app/avo/resources) directory.

## Resource Structure

Resources inherit from `Avo::BaseResource` which inherits from [lib/avo/resources/base.rb](mdc:lib/avo/resources/base.rb).

```ruby
class Avo::Resources::User < Avo::BaseResource
  # Resource configuration
  self.title = :name
  self.includes = [:posts]

  def fields
    field :id, as: :id
    field :name, as: :text, required: true
    field :email, as: :text
    field :created_at, as: :date_time
  end
end
```

## Field Declarations

Resources have multiple options and methods, with the most common being the `fields` method which holds all the field declarations.

### Field Declaration Pattern
In the `fields` method, users declare the attributes they want to see in the views using:

```ruby
field :field_name, as: :field_type, **options
```

### Common Field Options
- `required: true/false` - Mark field as required
- `readonly: true/false` - Make field read-only
- `help: "Help text"` - Add help text
- `placeholder: "Placeholder"` - Set input placeholder
- `default: value` - Set default value
- `hide_on: [:index, :show]` - Hide on specific views
- `show_on: [:edit, :new]` - Show only on specific views

### Example Field Declarations
```ruby
def fields
  field :id, as: :id
  field :name, as: :text, required: true, help: "User's full name"
  field :email, as: :text, placeholder: "user@example.com"
  field :admin, as: :boolean, default: false
  field :avatar, as: :file
  field :posts, as: :has_many
end
```
